data.title: Marines TV
data.meta_description: U.S. Navy corpsmen with 3rd Medical Battalion, 3rd Marine Logistics Group, conduct Role 2 light maneuver medical training at Combat Town, Central Training Area, Okinawa, Japan, June 7, 2022. 3rd MLG, based out of Okinawa, Japan, is a forward-deployed combat unit that serves as III Marine Expeditionary Force’s comprehensive logistics and combat service support backbone for operations throughout the Indo-Pacific area of responsibility. (U.S. Marine Corps photo by Cpl. Moises Rodriguez)
